By: Walter Hilton
---
No man is made suddenly sovereign in grace, but through long exercise
and sly working a soul may come thereto, namely when He helpeth and
teacheth a wretched soul in whom all grace lieth. for without special
help and inwardly teaching of Him may no soul come thereto.
